The List.get API cannot be used for getting the byte offset of a line in a text file. Instead, you can use the RandomAccessFile API to achieve this.

<<<api>>>: RandomAccessFile
<<<code>>>: RandomAccessFile file = new RandomAccessFile("file.txt", "r");
            long offset = 0;
            String line;
            while ((line = file.readLine()) != null) {
                // Process the line and get the offset
                offset = file.getFilePointer();
            }
            file.close();
<<<explanation>>>: Use the RandomAccessFile class to open the file in read mode. Read each line using the readLine() method until the end of the file is reached. The getFilePointer() method returns the current offset in the file. Store this offset for each line and process it as needed. Finally, close the file using the close() method.
